  "doc_id": "59633",
  "text": "Orthofinder (Brettanomyces + O. polymorpha) was used to find SCOs over these genomes. Protein sequences were aligned with Muscle v3.8.31 [CITATION_1] and then converted to codon-spaced alignments using PAL2NAL [CITATION_2] . Average nucleotide identities were estimated using panito commit: f65ba29 (github.com/sanger-pathogens/ panito). A rooted maximum likelihood phylogeny was generated with IQ-TREE [84] on the concatenated codon alignments. IQ-TREE was also used to generate gene trees for all SCOs, and then to generate a coalescence-based phylogeny from the SCO individual gene trees. Phylogenies were created using the same method for the Saccharomyces species + N. castellii (outgroup) to serve as a comparison.",
